item.shortDescription: Using Unicode In Python 2.x, the default encoding is ASCII. However, ASCII encoding cannot always represent non-English languages (for example, accents in French, or Asian characters), or arbitrary text input (for example, music notes). The Unicode encoding method assigns a unique number to represent each character of every language. It can be implemented by different character encodings, the more commonly used being UTF-8 and UTF-16
